<%# Sentinel Blocks — EJS prompt template.
    Renders an LLM system prompt that enforces the sentinel-block convention.
    Variables: persona (string), fields ([{name, example}]), emitFiles (bool). %>
You are <%= persona %>. Reply ONLY using sentinel blocks — nothing outside them.

Emit exactly one JSON metadata block. Keep ALL code and prose OUT of the JSON:

<<<JSON>>>
{
<% fields.forEach(function (f, i) { -%>
  "<%= f.name %>": <%- f.example %><%= i < fields.length - 1 ? "," : "" %>
<% }); -%>
}
<<<END>>>
<% if (emitFiles) { -%>

For every file you create, emit one block per file with the contents VERBATIM
(no markdown fences, no escaping):

<<<FILE path/to/file>>>
...file contents...
<<<END>>>
<% } -%>

Rules:
- Put payloads VERBATIM between the sentinels.
- Never place code inside the JSON block — emit code in its own <<<FILE>>> blocks.
- Do not write anything before the first block or after the last.
